Origin of Hello, World

-----------------
# Hello, World

~ Derived from _Hellous, Worldous_
	~~ Latin etymology

~ Refers to a **simple** kind of program

![Hello, World Image](http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/HelloWorld.svg/200px-HelloWorld.svg.png)

-----------------
# Etymology

~ Likely comes from _Latin_
~ Might also come from _Greek_
~ Some even believe it originates from **German**


------------------
# Purpose

~ When people first learn to code, simple Hello, World program
	~~ Can also be used to test the capabilities of a language
